text: Dear Cheryl, how about Swiss Roll or those normal chiffon cake need to be frost & piping can use plain or top flour?

answers.text: @poohbear1005 Hi there, would prefer to use cake flour for these cakes to give a soft and light texture. You can google Baking Taitai chocolate sponge cake (top recipe for frosting/piping) and in the post you will see my various frosted cakes using this recipe. Also google for Baking Taitai’s Hurricane Roll cake to take a look at my Swiss roll. Top flour is alike cake flour, slight difference in protein level so no problem to use when making cakes.
@poohbear1005 yes you are right it’s the blue packaging. 👍
@baking_taitai thank you dear! Shall make my order then💕

@poohbear1005 I can’t comment on Bob’s Red Mill as I’ve not tried it before. I have been using Blue Jacket Flour (@innobakesg) since 2015 and all these 5 years I’ve not tried any other brands of flour as Blue Jacket gives me satisfactory bakes all the time!

@baking_taitai ohhhhh....cake flour is still best texture after baked. How about some packaging named as Fine Pastry Flour from Bob's Red Mill? Meanwhile, I shall google to get more knowledge. Hope to hear from you soon dear ... thanks!
@baking_taitai dear, thank you & appreciated for sharing. And I had followed. The blue packaging is "Blue Jacket Cake & Pastry Flour". Is it correct?
